# Citation file for erdos-ant-verification.
#
# Recognized by Zenodo (auto-generates DOI metadata on release), GitHub
# (renders a "Cite this repository" sidebar button), and citation managers.
#
# Format: Citation File Format v1.2.0
# Specification: https://citation-file-format.github.io/

cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use this software in academic work, please cite it as below.
  The artifact is an executable verification of a published mathematical
  lower bound; please ALSO cite the primary mathematical sources listed
  under `references`.

type: software

title: >-
  erdos-ant-verification: An Executable Verification Artifact for the
  Sawin et al. Lower Bound on the Erdős Unit-Distance Exponent

abstract: >-
  An open-source Python implementation that computationally verifies the
  finite, checkable parts of the 2026 OpenAI/Sawin disproof of the Erdős
  planar unit-distance conjecture. Reproduces equation (2.2) of the
  remarks PDF (delta >= ~6.24e-38 for the explicit construction with
  T = {3,5,7,11,13,17}, S = {101, infinity}, L_T = Q(sqrt 5, sqrt 13,
  sqrt 17, sqrt 21, sqrt 33)) to within 0.014% relative error using
  mpmath at 200-bit precision. The artifact does NOT contain a new
  mathematical proof, does NOT construct the infinite Golod-Shafarevich
  tower, and has NOT been peer-reviewed. It is intended as a citable
  reproducibility artifact for the published numerical lower bound.

authors:
  - name: Flamehaven Labs
    website: 'https://github.com/Flamehaven-Labs'

version: 0.1.1
date-released: '2026-05-24'

url: 'https://github.com/Flamehaven-Labs/erdos-ant-verification'
repository-code: 'https://github.com/Flamehaven-Labs/erdos-ant-verification'

license: MIT

keywords:
  - erdos-unit-distance
  - algebraic-number-theory
  - golod-shafarevich
  - class-field-tower
  - discrete-geometry
  - combinatorics
  - reproducibility
  - executable-verification
  - mathematical-verification
  - mpmath
  - openai-research
  - sawin-construction

references:
  - type: report
    title: Planar Point Sets with Many Unit Distances
    authors:
      - name: OpenAI
    year: 2026
    url: 'https://cdn.openai.com/pdf/74c24085-19b0-4534-9c90-465b8e29ad73/unit-distance-proof.pdf'
    notes: >-
      Primary mathematical source. Contains the AI-generated proof of
      Theorem 1.1 disproving the Erdős unit-distance conjecture.

  - type: report
    title: Remarks on the Disproof of the Unit Distance Conjecture
    authors:
      - family-names: Alon
        given-names: Noga
      - family-names: Bloom
        given-names: Thomas F.
      - family-names: Gowers
        given-names: W. T.
      - family-names: Litt
        given-names: Daniel
      - family-names: Sawin
        given-names: Will
      - family-names: Shankar
        given-names: Arul
      - family-names: Tsimerman
        given-names: Jacob
      - family-names: Wang
        given-names: Victor
      - family-names: Matchett Wood
        given-names: Melanie
    year: 2026
    url: 'https://cdn.openai.com/pdf/74c24085-19b0-4534-9c90-465b8e29ad73/unit-distance-remarks.pdf'
    notes: >-
      Primary mathematical source. Contains the human-digested, simplified
      construction including equation (2.2) which this artifact reproduces
      numerically.

  - type: article
    title: On sets of distances of n points
    authors:
      - family-names: Erdős
        given-names: Paul
    year: 1946
    journal: American Mathematical Monthly
    volume: 53
    issue: 5
    start: 248
    end: 250
    notes: >-
      Historical origin. Introduces the unit-distance problem and the
      conjectured upper bound n^(1 + O(1/log log n)) that the 2026
      disproof refutes.

  - type: article
    title: 'On the class field tower'
    authors:
      - family-names: Golod
        given-names: E. S.
      - family-names: Shafarevich
        given-names: I. R.
    year: 1964
    notes: >-
      Classical theorem. A finite pro-p group with d generators and r
      relations satisfying r <= d^2/4 is infinite. Used in the existence
      of the infinite class field tower (which this artifact does NOT
      construct explicitly).

  - type: book
    title: 'Primes of the form x^2 + n y^2: Fermat, class field theory, and complex multiplication'
    authors:
      - family-names: Cox
        given-names: David A.
    year: 1989
    publisher:
      name: Wiley
    notes: >-
      Background for the Phase 2 module: genus theory description of
      the Hilbert class field of Q(sqrt(-5)).
